preIndexProcessTags

public void preIndexProcessTags(oracle.ecsf.meta.SearchableObject so,
                                java.util.Map params,
                                java.util.List<oracle.ecsf.IndexableDocument> docs)
Hook into the pre index process of the crawl so we can annotate the SVO with tagging information (if any). This looks for child documents called tagSVO, which is the applcore public tag lookup VO. This should be joined to the SearchVO with as viewLink using the TAG_SERVICE_ID and TAG_RESOURCE_ID.

Parameters:
so - the searchable object definition.
params - to the plugin.
docs - Documents to iterate and find tag children for.

preIndexProcessAttachments

public void preIndexProcessAttachments(oracle.ecsf.meta.SearchableObject so,
                                       java.util.Map params,
                                       java.util.List<oracle.ecsf.IndexableDocument> docs)
Hook into the pre index process of the crawl so we can annotate the SVO with additional attachment information.

This method does not actually add the attachment, this is done by ECSF internally (see class FusionAppsExtension). This method will find all attachments in the Document tree and add additonal attributes to the parent (root) indexed document so that the search UI can display the individual attachments, and allow the user to click on them to obtain their content.
This information is otherwise lost as the attachment is essentially inlined with the document.

Parameters:
so - the searchable object.
params - parameters for the plugin.
docs - Documents to iterate and find attachment descedents for.
See Also:
oracle.ecsf.fusion.FusionAppsExtension#createAttachment
